comments.body:
Thanks for the feedback, @TrevorBenson! I totally agree. It's a reoccurring issue and I stepped into the trap many times. Podman inherited these commands from Docker and I believe it was a mistake to put the commands on the same level. A `podman {container,image} {save,load}` may be much easier to wrap the head around as the "container" and "image" sub-command give the context.

I like your idea to have a look at the man pages and `--help` texts. The latter may even highlight that difference to the container/image counterpart.

@TrevorBenson, are you interested in opening a PR?
